FBIS4-29266 "dreas116_d_94012" FBIS-EAS-94-116 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 South Korea Russia: Five N. Koreans `Unwelcome' Diplomats Russia: Five N. Koreans `Unwelcome' Diplomats SK1606022394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0133 GMT 16 Jun 94 SK1606022394 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network Korean BFN [Text] It has been revealed that the five North Koreans who were recently deported from Russia for attempting to obtain nuclear materials [haek mulchil] were diplomats. (Basilev), spokesman for the Counter-Intelligence Headquarters of the Russian Federation, said today that the five North Koreans who tried to obtain materials [mulchil] for use in manufacturing nuclear weapons were designated as figures to be avoided [kipi inmul], that is, unwelcome diplomats in the country where they work, and were deported from Russia in the spring.
